Date: Mon, 21 Apr 2026 23:30:00 +0530
Subject: fix: use bundled devtools frontend URL for remote debugging

When using --remote-debugging-port, the DevTools HTTP handler constructs
a devtoolsFrontendUrl included in the /json response. Chrome's
chrome://inspect page uses this URL to load the DevTools frontend when
the user clicks "Inspect".

Previously, the URL was only set to the local bundled path
(/devtools/inspector.html) when CHROMIUM_GIT_REVISION was missing
(all zeros). When a real git revision was present—as is always the case
in Electron builds—the URL pointed to Google's CDN
(chrome-devtools-frontend.appspot.com). If the CDN did not have the
exact revision (common for Electron's custom Chromium builds), Chrome
would receive a 404 and the DevTools page would appear empty.

This patch changes the condition to prefer the bundled frontend URL
whenever HasBundledFrontendResources() returns true, regardless of the
git revision. The remote CDN URL is now only used as a fallback when
bundled resources are not available.

Fixes: https://github.com/electron/electron/issues/51035

diff --git a/content/browser/devtools/devtools_http_handler.cc b/content/browser/devtools/devtools_http_handler.cc
--- a/content/browser/devtools/devtools_http_handler.cc
+++ b/content/browser/devtools/devtools_http_handler.cc
@@ -544,8 +544,7 @@ std::string DevToolsHttpHandler::GetFrontendURLInternal(
     const std::string& host) {
   std::string frontend_url;
   const std::string git_revision = CHROMIUM_GIT_REVISION;
-  if (git_revision == kMissingGitRevision &&
-      delegate_->HasBundledFrontendResources()) {
+  if (delegate_->HasBundledFrontendResources()) {
     frontend_url = "/devtools/inspector.html";
   } else {
     std::string type = agent_host->GetType();
